{
    "info": {
        "_postman_id": "grhapoch-fcm-push-notifications",
        "name": "GrhaPoch — FCM Push Notifications",
        "description": "Complete test suite for FCM push notification token management.\n\n## How to use\n1. Import this collection into Postman\n2. Run the **Login** request for the role you want to test\n3. The token is auto-saved to a collection variable\n4. Run Save / Remove token requests — they use the saved token automatically\n\n## Roles covered\n- **User** — customer app\n- **Delivery** — delivery partner app\n- **Restaurant** — restaurant owner app\n\n## Anti-double-notification verification\nThe backend uses `sendEachForMulticast` with a `tag` key in the data payload.\nThe service worker uses the same `tag` to replace existing notifications instead of stacking them.",
        "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
    },
    "variable": [
        {
            "key": "base_url",
            "value": "http://localhost:5000/api",
            "type": "string"
        },
        {
            "key": "user_token",
            "value": "",
            "type": "string"
        },
        {
            "key": "delivery_token",
            "value": "",
            "type": "string"
        },
        {
            "key": "restaurant_token",
            "value": "",
            "type": "string"
        },
        {
            "key": "fake_fcm_token_web",
            "value": "fcm_fake_web_token_for_testing_{{$randomUUID}}",
            "type": "string"
        },
        {
            "key": "fake_fcm_token_mob",
            "value": "fcm_fake_mobile_token_for_testing_{{$randomUUID}}",
            "type": "string"
        }
    ],
    "item": [
        {
            "name": "🔑 1. Login (Get Auth Tokens)",
            "item": [
                {
                    "name": "Login — User (Email+Password)",
                    "event": [
                        {
                            "listen": "test",
                            "script": {
                                "exec": [
                                    "const res = pm.response.json();",
                                    "if (res.accessToken) {",
                                    "  pm.collectionVariables.set('user_token', res.accessToken);",
                                    "  console.log('✅ User token saved');",
                                    "} else if (res.data && res.data.accessToken) {",
                                    "  pm.collectionVariables.set('user_token', res.data.accessToken);",
                                    "  console.log('✅ User token saved (nested)');",
                                    "} else {",
                                    "  console.warn('⚠️ No accessToken found — check credentials');",
                                    "}",
                                    "pm.test('Login successful', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
                                ],
                                "type": "text/javascript"
                            }
                        }
                    ],
                    "request": {
                        "method": "POST",
                        "header": [
                            {
                                "key": "Content-Type",
                                "value": "application/json"
                            }
                        ],
                        "body": {
                            "mode": "raw",
                            "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"YOUR_USER_EMAIL@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"YOUR_USER_PASSWORD\",\n  \"role\": \"user\"\n}"
                        },
                        "url": {
                            "raw": "{{base_url}}/login",
                            "host": [
                                "{{base_url}}"
                            ],
                            "path": [
                                "login"
                            ]
                        }
                    },
                    "_postman_description": "Replace email/password with a real user account. The token is auto-saved to `user_token`."
                },
                {
                    "name": "Login — User (OTP — Step 1: Send OTP)",
                    "request": {
