                    "_postman_description": "## How to send a real push notification\n\nFrom any backend controller, use:\n\n```js\nimport { sendPushNotification } from '../services/fcmAdminService.js';\n\n// Get real token from DB\nconst user = await User.findById(userId);\nif (user.fcmTokens?.length) {\n  await sendPushNotification(user.fcmTokens, {\n    title: 'Test 🔔',\n    body: 'Push notification is working!',\n    data: {\n      type: 'test',\n      link: '/'\n    }\n  });\n}\n```\n\n## Anti-double-notification\nEach notification gets a unique `tag` in the `data` field.\nThe service worker uses this tag to **replace** existing notifications instead of stacking them.\nThe foreground handler uses an in-memory Set with 5s TTL for the same reason."
